reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 3, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I ordered these pocket folders for a women's retreat that I am hosting later this year. The rainbow colors were what attracted me to the folders, initially. When they arrived, I was pleased with the quality. They seem to be a little nicer than the dollar store type folder. The pockets inside seem sturdy and that was what I was looking for. The folders can hold a number of papers, and keep them inside. I'm happy with these folders and am sure they will work well for my purpose.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Back to school shopping done!
reviews.reviewText: My sons' school requires plastic poly folders in lieu of paper folders so that they hold up longer, and I find myself having to shop multiple stores to get the right colors because inevitably each store will only have one color in stock. The folders are also not to have any prongs or other superfluous "accessories". I was so thrilled to find a set of these folders, 2 in each color, to satisfy the school supply list for 2 kids months ahead of time! Back to school shopping will be much easier this year!These folders are similar to the mid-high quality poly folders at most big box stores. They aren't quite as thick as a Mead poly folder, but very close.
